r> <font color=#000033>(2/14/02 7:04:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1693.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/cyks/redshoes.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I Fucking Hate You ALL!</span><hr size=1> if i was a driver, and got stiffed(been there, done that)... YES, i would be upset, but would move along to my next delivery. Disappointed, nah..i wouldn't get all emotional about it. Down right pissed? nope, never... Now if someone came to their door, opened it, snatched the pizza, didn't pay and slam the door...yeah, then I would be pissed. lol, but that never happened to me.<br>
<br>
As for not tipping the driver, it is not RUDE! It's the consumers choice. I, having been there.. know all the timelines on how to make a pizza. I know it takes 1 min to take an order, 1 min to make a pizza... (5 min if its during a rush) I know the oven cooks em at bout 8.5 mins. Shit, I will give you 15 min to get it all put together and cooked. <br>
<br>
Yet, I was still quoted 45 min to have it delivered. Fine, I was the one who didn't want to bundle up the kids and go out. So that gives the driver 30 min to get it to my house. Yep, you have other deliverys, but once mine is outta the oven...it should be in route to the house. If it takes a company longer than that, yes, a lot will stiff you... and thats not rude. The consumer was lied to from the beginning.<br>
<br>
Then again, you will have the same costomer, Mr.  Joe, who lives right around the corner, orders every week, and always has exact change, never ever tips. Do you get pissed at him? No, you realize this, drop off the pizza and rush to your next one. Now you say Mr. Joe should pick up his pizza if he can't tip... do you think of the consumers position? Did you think he walks with a cane, and it's slick as can be outside, ice all over.. He could have a touch of the flew, and doesn' want to make it worse... PLUS, he's on a budget, the money he makes doesn't allow him to give away a dollar a week to you. That small little dollar, means 10 x's more to him than you. sooo, is that RUDE? Shoud he refuse the &quot;free&quot; delivery service because of this? NOPE, he shouldn't, NOPE, it's not rude.<br>
<br>
I think it has more to do with the company than the drivers... I have a coupon for 9.99...if on the phone, I am asked do I want it delivered, then am told the price is 10.99 $1 for delivery... well then, in most peoples mind, you already made that $1, your lucky if you get more. (remember, they don't know you are not getting that whole dollar) So from the consumers viewpoint, it is not rude at all not to tip you, they think they already have. <br>
<br>
Same thing, i have that 9.99 coupon, would you like &quot;free&quot; delivery with that, yes... well its 9.99 ....I think the drivers would benifit more that way. But even if they tip you or not... it is not required at all, and not rude if they don't. They know you will recieve a paycheck either way.<br>
<br>
so I donot think it is RUDE if they don't. I also don't think people are not being polite...as explained  above, I believe most &quot;think&quot; they have already tipped you. <br>
